        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 6:31PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 631 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Longmont, or 27 miles southwest of Greeley, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thornton, northeastern Westminster, northeastern Boulder,
Longmont, northeastern Broomfield, Commerce City, northern
Northglenn, Brighton, Lafayette, Erie, Firestone, Frederick,
Dacono, Mead, Platteville, Niwot, Todd Creek, Hygiene and Fort St
Vrain.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
